  "body": "From: https://discord.com/channels/629004402170134531/629004402170134537/965954507483779172\r\n\r\n\"When troubleshooting internet connectivity issues I noticed my nethermind instances (mainnet & goerli) sometimes send UDP payloads which need to be fragmented.\r\nThis is an issue for my shitty Cable bridge (don't ask), but also in general appears to be something which is best avoided. Is this intended to happen or maybe a bug?\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12445221/164346231-0e818aae-f8df-41cc-9a8a-40c52e217ff8.png)\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/devp2p/blob/master/discv4.md#wire-protocol says The maximum size of any packet is 1280 bytes. ... then this would clearly be a bug?\r\n\r\nFrom what I can say, those messages seem to all have 0x04 at index 0x61, which seems to indicate they are NeighborsMsg.\r\nis the UDP payload enough?\"\r\n\r\nExample payloads for investigation:\r\n[nethermind-discov4-large-udp-payloads.txt](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/files/8526283/nethermind-discov4-large-udp-payloads.txt)",
